  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "Attending the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, often referred to as the \"Woodstock for Capitalists,\" is a unique opportunity for shareholders to hear directly from Warren Buffett and Charlie Munger, network with fellow investors, and gain insights into the company's performance and future plans. Here are the key requirements and steps to attend the meeting:\n\n### **1. Own Berkshire Hathaway Shares by the Record Date**\n- **Shareholder Status:** To be eligible to attend, you must own Berkshire Hathaway Class A (BRK.A) or Class B (BRK.B) shares by the specified record date. This date is typically announced well in advance of the meeting.\n- **Verification:** Ensure your shares are registered in your name or held in a brokerage account that can verify your ownership to Berkshire Hathaway.\n\n### **2. Register for the Meeting**\n- **Registration Process:** Berkshire Hathaway typically requires shareholders to register for the meeting. This process may involve submitting your contact information and confirming your eligibility based on your shareholding.\n- **Ticket Allocation:** Due to the high demand and limited seating (often capped at around 40,000 attendees), registration is competitive. Berkshire Hathaway may use a lottery system or first-come, first-served basis to allocate tickets.\n  \n### **3. Provide Proof of Ownership**\n- **Documentation:** You may need to provide proof of your Berkshire Hathaway share ownership when registering or upon arrival. This can include:\n  - A recent brokerage statement showing your holdings.\n  - A shareholder statement from Berkshire Hathaway.\n  - Other official documentation verifying your status as a shareholder.\n\n### **4. Comply with Event Policies**\n- **Health and Safety Guidelines:** Depending on current health guidelines and policies, you might need to comply with specific health and safety measures, such as mask-wearing or providing proof of vaccination. Always check the latest requirements closer to the event date.\n- **Conduct Rules:** Adhere to the event\u2019s code of conduct, which typically emphasizes respectful behavior, no solicitation, and limits on photography or recording.\n\n### **5. Attend the Meeting**\n- **Location and Timing:** The meeting is traditionally held at the Berkshire Hathaway headquarters in Omaha, Nebraska, at **The CHI Health Center Omaha** (formerly known as the Omaha Convention Center). Ensure you have travel accommodations arranged well in advance, as the event attracts attendees from all over the world.\n- **Schedule:** The meeting usually spans a full day, starting in the morning and concluding in the evening, with presentations, Q&A sessions, and social gatherings.\n\n### **6. Plan Ahead Due to High Demand**\n- **Early Preparation:** Given the popularity of the event, it\u2019s crucial to start the registration and planning process early once details are announced. Information about the record date, registration process, and meeting specifics are typically communicated to shareholders several months in advance.\n- **Stay Informed:** Keep an eye on official Berkshire Hathaway communications, such as shareholder letters, the company website, or communications from your broker, for the latest updates and detailed instructions.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n- **Travel Arrangements:** Book flights and accommodations as early as possible to secure the best rates and availability.\n- **Local Transportation:** Familiarize yourself with the local transportation options in Omaha to navigate easily on the day of the meeting.\n- **Networking Opportunities:** Be prepared to network with other investors and attendees, which can be a valuable aspect of the meeting experience.\n\n### **Official Resources:**\n- **Berkshire Hathaway Website:** Visit the official [Berkshire Hathaway website](https://www.berkshirehathaway.com/) for the latest information and updates regarding the annual shareholder meeting.\n- **Shareholder Communications:** Refer to correspondence from Berkshire Hathaway, including the annual shareholder letter, for specific details related to the upcoming meeting.\n\nBy meeting these requirements and planning ahead, you can increase your chances of successfully attending the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting and fully enjoying this prestigious event.",
